# .trivyignore — unfixable OS-level CVEs with justifications
# All entries here have Status: "affected" or "fix_deferred" with no fixed version
# available in Debian 13 (Bookworm) as of 2026-06-24.
# Reviewed and accepted as risk for demo environment.
# Production action: monitor Debian security tracker and patch when fix is released.

# ncurses — CVE-2025-69720
# Buffer overflow in ncurses. No fixed version available in Debian 13.
# ncurses is a base package that cannot be removed from python:3.11-slim.
# Exploitability is low — ncurses is a terminal library, not directly exposed.
CVE-2025-69720

# SQLite — CVE-2026-11822, CVE-2026-11824
# Memory corruption in SQLite. No fixed version available in Debian 13.
# SQLite is bundled with Python and cannot be independently upgraded.
# Not directly used by this application.
CVE-2026-11822
CVE-2026-11824
